how to make caramel how to make caramel why my caramel always tastes bitter delicious caramel recipe cup water cup plus tablespoon sugar tablespoons light corn syrup cup heavy cream warmed to degrees f cup creme fraiche teaspoon fresh lemon juice pinch salt less than teaspoon heat a saucepan of water and place a whisk in it wash and dry your hands thoroughly combine the water cup of sugar and the corn syrup in a medium saucepan stir them together with very clean fingers making sure no lumps of dry sugar remain brush down the insides of the pan with a little water using your hand to feel for any stray granules of sugar cover the saucepan and place it over medium heat for minutes after minutes remove the lid increase the heat to high and bring to a boil do not stir from this point on keep an eye on the pan it will be very bubbly when stray sugar crystals appear on the side of the pan brush them down with a wet pastry brush as the sugar cooks the bubbles will get larger insert a candy thermometer and when the temperature reaches degrees f lower the heat to medium which will slow the cooking continue to cook the sugar until it reaches degrees f it will be dark brown remove the pot from the heat and let it sit for minute or until the bubbles subside add the cream to the caramel it will bubble up vigorously so be careful vigorously whisk in the remaining tablespoon sugar creme fraiche lemon juice and salt this sauce is now ready to be served warm or cooled to room temperature it will keep stored airtight in the refrigerator for up to month when cold it has the consistency of peanut butter Humidor Cigar Plastic Poker jargon Hard disk Floppy disk Digital photography Wal-Mart Hamster Movie projector Money Tofu Carburetor M16 (rifle) Microeconomics Electrophysiology Surveillance Cruising (maritime) Futurama (TV series - season 5) Scuba set RISC Coffee CPU cache Cannabis cultivation Bulk vending Sampling (music) Strap-on dildo Effect of Hurricane Katrina on New Orleans Broadba